            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>He was ordered to change places with the Jews. *</p>
<p>A Jewish friend helps me understand:</p>
<p>&ldquo;I didn&rsquo;t suffer. I don&rsquo;t suffer. My grandmother and grandfather suffered. Please don&rsquo;t invalidate their experiences.&rdquo;</p>
<p>And a hateful e-mail provokes deep concern:</p>
<p>&ldquo;Jews are out to control the world, Philip. Don&rsquo;t believe those who try to deny this fact. I am glad that you have supported the white supremacist&rsquo;s right to speak!&rdquo;</p>
<p>Intentions cannot always be discerned through the mask of language. I wanted to start a dialogue about human suffering, but instead I ripped open old wounds, to fuel the very anti-Semitism that caused them. For this, I am deeply sorry. It is my failure as a columnist, and as a student. Our failure as a community is the dishearteningly narrow space we reserve for transformative conversation.</p>
<p>DOUBT</p>
<p>More vitriol to my in-box:</p>

                                                    <div class="related my-4 py-4 d-print-none">
                                <h3 class="kicker mb-4">Read more</h3>

                                                                                                                
            
        
